modules.description: This module implements an extension for inline test cases using Alcotest, allowing tests to be embedded directly within code. It provides functions to parse and expand test expressions into executable test structures, supporting conditional test dropping based on location. Key data types include expressions, structures, and attributes from Ppxlib, used to manipulate and generate OCaml AST nodes for inline testing.

This module defines functions to programmatically add and execute inline Alcotest test cases. It works with test functions of type `unit -> unit` and organizes them under string-identified paths and names. Concrete use cases include embedding test definitions directly within library modules and running them without external test harnesses.
